This paper deals with routing in a geometric setting, specifically in orthogonal polygons. This suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses routing with preprocessing and labels, which is a common topic in the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The use of routing tables and headers also suggests a possible connection to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the number of bits required for labels and routing tables, which is a topic in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
